    "postDate": "2026-06-02T22:02:31.337Z",
    "rawMarkdown": "May I ask what is \"target\" and \"score\"? Do you somehow estimate the \"ideal\" score that you want to reach, calculated using some heuristics?\n\nJust tried to submit your exact 15 tasks, ours reaches 232.16 pts (as opposed to yours 227.716).\n\nThis is actually remarkable. Our team focused more on mid-tier and lower-tier tasks until last week, and you seem to excel in easy-tier tasks (we have quite a bit less 20+ points than you)\n\n![](https://www.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/kaggle-forum-message-attachments/o/inbox%2F2270821%2F98544a55d149d952b4f3d6b3e3cb2983%2FUntitled.png?generation=1780437606997057&alt=media)\n",
    "content": "<p>May I ask what is \"target\" and \"score\"? Do you somehow estimate the \"ideal\" score that you want to reach, calculated using some heuristics?</p>\n<p>Just tried to submit your exact 15 tasks, ours reaches 232.16 pts (as opposed to yours 227.716).</p>\n<p>This is actually remarkable. Our team focused more on mid-tier and lower-tier tasks until last week, and you seem to excel in easy-tier tasks (we have quite a bit less 20+ points than you)</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/kaggle-forum-message-attachments/o/inbox%2F2270821%2F98544a55d149d952b4f3d6b3e3cb2983%2FUntitled.png?generation=1780437606997057&amp;alt=media\" alt=\"\"></p>",
    "replies": [
     {
      "id": 3465832,
      "postDate": "2026-06-02T22:14:11.703Z",
      "rawMarkdown": "Your 232.16 on the same 15 tasks is very strong — thanks for checking. That confirms there is still real headroom in my bottom tasks. I’m trying to close that gap step by step , this is very useful to know.\n\nThanks again, and good luck!\n\nabout target score , The “target” is just a heuristic, not an exact ideal score.\n\nI set my total goal around 7750, then estimate each task’s target based on my current score distribution, how easy/hard the task looks, and how much room it may still have. High-score tasks likely have less room, low-score tasks may have more.\n\nSo it’s mostly score distribution + easy/hard guessing + what I need to reach the total target.\n",
      "content": "<p>Your 232.16 on the same 15 tasks is very strong — thanks for checking. That confirms there is still real headroom in my bottom tasks. I’m trying to close that gap step by step , this is very useful to know.</p>\n<p>Thanks again, and good luck!</p>\n<p>about target score , The “target” is just a heuristic, not an exact ideal score.</p>\n<p>I set my total goal around 7750, then estimate each task’s target based on my current score distribution, how easy/hard the task looks, and how much room it may still have. High-score tasks likely have less room, low-score tasks may have more.</p>\n<p>So it’s mostly score distribution + easy/hard guessing + what I need to reach the total target.</p>",
