        "id": 3465909,
        "postDate": "2026-06-03T02:36:06.430Z",
        "rawMarkdown": "> > how easy/hard the task looks, and how much room it may still have\n> \n> Just curious, how do you estimate this? Have tried doing that and it was so inaccurate 😂\n\nHonestly, it’s not a real estimate. It’s more like a made-up target for the LLM to chase — we could use almost any number.\n\nI just asked ChatGPT to use last year’s Python byte length / score as a rough reference, then generate code or ideas around that. The number keeps changing anyway, so it’s more of a prompt anchor 😂\n\nThe LLM will probably never truly “hit” the goal, because once it gets close, the next standard just moves higher.",
        "content": "<blockquote>\n  <blockquote>\n    <p>how easy/hard the task looks, and how much room it may still have</p>\n  </blockquote>\n  <p>Just curious, how do you estimate this? Have tried doing that and it was so inaccurate 😂</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Honestly, it’s not a real estimate. It’s more like a made-up target for the LLM to chase — we could use almost any number.</p>\n<p>I just asked ChatGPT to use last year’s Python byte length / score as a rough reference, then generate code or ideas around that. The number keeps changing anyway, so it’s more of a prompt anchor 😂</p>\n<p>The LLM will probably never truly “hit” the goal, because once it gets close, the next standard just moves higher.</p>",
